pos_mean_info_list.mean: 给…薪水（salary的过去式和过去分词）

word_mean_info__list.difference: 指提供某种服务收取的固定费用。
多指通过劳动或投资等手段所得到的收入。
多用复数形式，指按小时、日或星期的报酬，通常指体力劳动者的工资。
与earnings含义很相近，但前者强调总收入。
指按年定下，按月或星期平均给予的报酬，指脑力劳动者的薪水。

bilingual.source: His salary is paid once a month.
bilingual.target: 他的薪水每月发放一次。

bilingual.source: He is very satisfied with his salary.
The CEO's salary is usually very high.
bilingual.target: 首席执行官的薪水通常很高。

bilingual.source: Her salary has increased compared to last year.
bilingual.target: 她的薪水比去年增加了。

bilingual.source: They complain about the company's low salary.
bilingual.target: 他们抱怨公司的薪水菲薄。

bilingual.source: She earns a good salary at her new job.
bilingual.target: 她在新工作中赚取了不错的薪水。

bilingual.source: The salary for this job can be discussed personally.
bilingual.target: 这份工作的薪水可以面议。

bilingual.source: He quit the job because of the low salary.
bilingual.target: 他因为薪水菲薄而辞去了那份工作。

bilingual.source: The salary of a senior accountant is usually high.
bilingual.target: 高级会计师的薪水通常很高。

bilingual.source: She hopes to find a job with a higher salary.
bilingual.target: 她希望找到一份薪水更高的工作。

list.abstract: salary是指非体力劳动者所得到的“工资、薪水”，通常按月，有时按季或年计算（Salary is usually paid monthly,sometimes three months or a year,for a job,esp.as for workers of higher skill and rank）

yingyinNormal.en: The salary, per his demand, was 25 cents. One quarter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 按照他的意愿，薪水是25美分。一枚硬币。

yingyinNormal.en: Report to work Monday morning. And you will receive a salary and a pension.
yingyinNormal.zh: 周一早上你去上班报到就会领薪水和年金了。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《爱丽丝梦游仙境2：镜中奇遇记》

yingyinNormal.en: You have that? Anything you need to help you find that egg, and then there's the salary.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你还有这个？只要能帮你找到彩蛋的我都有，还附带薪水。

yingyinNormal.en: Imagine that you are out of school and you've been offered a salary of 70,000 dollars.
yingyinNormal.zh: 假如你踏入社会年薪七万美金。

yingyinNormal.en: We're living off of a gym teacher's salary, and somehow I let you talk me into buying the apartment upstairs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们靠着一个体育老师的工资生活，然后我还不知道哪根筋搭错了被你说服买下了楼上的房子。

yingyinNormal.en: Jackie, you have repeatedly opposed the minimum-wage and CEO salary bill I asked the leadership to introduce.
yingyinNormal.zh: 杰姬，你一再反对我想让领导层推行的《最低工资和高管薪酬标准法案》。

yingyinNormal.en: How do you know? Well, on your salary, it would have to be modest, and you spent all the money on that cottage, didn't you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你怎么知道？凭你的工资，你不能过得太阔绰，而且你把钱都花在那间农舍上了吧？

yingyinNormal.en: You don't need your dad's money. You can get by on your salary. Yeah. Well, we work at the same place as you, and we've always been fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你才不需要你爸的钱。你的收入足够养活你自己了。没错。我们和你一样都在学校工作，我们就活得挺好。

yingyinNormal.en: Listen, there's no salary. No. I was not aware of that. My circumstances have changed some and I need to be certain that I'll be... All right. Okay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实习期没有工资。没有。我并不知道没有工资，现在我的处境变了，我需要确定我能... 好的。

yingyinNormal.en: You gotta take this offer. What? Higher salary, better benefits. I mean, you might have to travel more, which is time away from Phil. Nothing but upside.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你得接受这份工作。什么？工资更高，福利更好。你可能得经常出差，那就意味着要离开菲尔。全是好处。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指脑力劳动所得的报酬，如工程师、教师、政府官员、管理人员等的固定薪金，可按周、按月、按季或按年领取。
泛指所得的报酬，为不可数名词。
比pay更加正式，是可数名词，而且经常用复数。
指体力劳动所得的报酬，如熟练工人、售货员等的固定工资，可按小时、按天、或按周领取。
